sdp/verification/t-005@20260515t214233z-verify.md:15:Implementation matches the spec precisely. `PALKnowledgeChunk` is a `frozen=True` dataclass with all seven specified fields. `chunk_pal_source_files` delegates source ordering to `discover_pal_source_files` (inheriting its deterministic sort), normalises line endings via `splitlines()`, skips whitespace-only files, and packs complete lines up to `max_chars`. Overlong lines are split deterministically by offset. `chunk_id` is derived solely from `source_path`, `source_sha256`, `chunk_index`, `start_line`, `end_line`, and `text` — no wall-clock time or mutable runtime state included. Source paths are POSIX-relative-to-root for in-project files and absolute POSIX otherwise.
sdp/verification/t-005@20260515t214233z-verify.md:34:Follows established project patterns: stdlib-only, no runtime side effects, no new dependencies. Private helpers (`_normalize_text`, `_source_reference`, `_chunk_text`, `_make_chunk`) follow the underscore-prefix convention used throughout `pal_knowledge.py`. `PALKnowledgeChunk` sits beside `discover_pal_source_files` in the same module per the spec. Test helpers (`_save_pal_config`, `_chunk_ids_by_source`) follow the same private-function convention used in existing tests. No `.promptclaw/pal-kb/` directory is created — PAL-015 owns the index writer.
